#PGML

BEGIN_PGML

In each of the following scenarios find the angular momentum of the rod or disc about their
center of gravity [`G`] and about point [`O`].

[@ image( "22-R-IM-JL-32.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*


Scenario 1: The disc has radius [`r = [$r]\ \textrm{cm}`], mass [`m = [$m1]\ \textrm{g}`] and rolls with angular velocity [`\vec \omega = -[$w1]\ \hat{k}\ \textrm{rad/s}`]. 

[`\vec H_{G_1} = `] [________]{"$HG1"} [`\hat{k}\ \textrm{kg·m}^2\textrm{/s}`]

[`\vec H_{O_1} = `] [________]{"$HO1"} [`\hat{k}\ \textrm{kg·m}^2\textrm{/s}`]  

_ㅤ_

Scenario 2: The rod has length [`L = [$L]\ \textrm{cm}`], mass [`m = [$m2]\ \textrm{g}`] and rotates with angular velocity [`\vec \omega = -[$w2]\ \hat{k}\ \textrm{rad/s}`]. 

[`\vec H_{G_2} = `] [________]{"$HG2"} [`\hat{k}\ \textrm{kg·m}^2\textrm{/s}`]

[`\vec H_{O_2} = `] [________]{"$HO2"} [`\hat{k}\ \textrm{kg·m}^2\textrm{/s}`]  

_ㅤ_

Scenario 3: The rod has length [`d = [$d]\ \textrm{cm}`], mass [`m = [$m3]\ \textrm{g}`] and rotates with angular velocity [`\vec \omega = [$w3]\ \hat{k}\ \textrm{rad/s}`]. 

[`\vec H_{G_3} = `] [________]{"$HG3"} [`\hat{k}\ \textrm{kg·m}^2\textrm{/s}`]

[`\vec H_{O_3} = `] [________]{"$HO3"} [`\hat{k}\ \textrm{kg·m}^2\textrm{/s}`]

